               <p>RICHARD WALLACE. I was in <placeName id="t18300415-366-crimeloc1982">Fleet-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-366-crimeloc1982" type="placeName" value="Fleet-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-366-crimeloc1982" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-366-off1980 t18300415-366-crimeloc1982"></join>, opposite Chancery-lane, at half-past seven o'clock on the evening in question, and felt some one at my pocket; I sprang round, and caught the prisoner putting my handkerchief under his jacket - I had been walking with my wife and sister; it has my initials, and No. 3 on it - this is it; there were several persons passing, but none in his company.</p>
